sequenceDiagram
    participant Client as External Client
    participant Router as OpenShift Router<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS1.2+
    participant Gateway as Istio Ingress Gateway<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS1.2+
    participant Authorino as Authorino<br/>50051/TCP gRPC mTLS
    participant K8sAPI as Kubernetes API<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant Envoy as Istio Envoy Sidecar<br/>mTLS (ISTIO_MUTUAL)
    participant REST as REST Container<br/>8080/TCP HTTP
    participant GRPC as gRPC Container<br/>9090/TCP gRPC
    participant DB as PostgreSQL/MySQL<br/>5432/3306 TCP

    Note over Client,DB: Flow 1: External Client → Model Registry REST API (with Istio)

    Client->>Router: POST /api/model_registry/v1alpha3/registered_models<br/>Authorization: Bearer {token}
    Router->>Gateway: Forward HTTPS Request<br/>TLS 1.2+
    Gateway->>Authorino: ext-authz gRPC<br/>Bearer Token (forwarded)
    Authorino->>K8sAPI: TokenReview API<br/>Validate JWT token
    K8sAPI-->>Authorino: Token Valid
    Authorino->>K8sAPI: SubjectAccessReview<br/>Check GET on service/{registry-name}
    K8sAPI-->>Authorino: Authorized
    Authorino-->>Gateway: Authorization Approved
    Gateway->>Envoy: HTTP Request<br/>mTLS (ISTIO_MUTUAL)
    Envoy->>REST: HTTP/8080<br/>Plaintext (localhost)
    REST->>GRPC: gRPC/9090<br/>MLMD API Call
    GRPC->>DB: SQL Query<br/>TLS (optional sslmode)
    DB-->>GRPC: Model Metadata
    GRPC-->>REST: MLMD Response
    REST-->>Envoy: JSON Response
    Envoy-->>Gateway: mTLS Response
    Gateway-->>Router: HTTPS Response
    Router-->>Client: 200 OK

    Note over Client,DB: Flow 2: Operator Reconciliation Loop

    participant Operator as Controller Manager<br/>Service Account Token

    Operator->>K8sAPI: Watch ModelRegistry CRs<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS1.2+
    K8sAPI-->>Operator: ModelRegistry Created/Updated
    Operator->>K8sAPI: Create Deployment<br/>HTTPS TLS1.2+
    Operator->>K8sAPI: Create Service<br/>8080, 9090
    Operator->>K8sAPI: Create ServiceAccount
    Operator->>K8sAPI: Create RBAC Role/Binding

    alt Istio Enabled
        Operator->>K8sAPI: Create Istio Gateway
        Operator->>K8sAPI: Create VirtualService
        Operator->>K8sAPI: Create DestinationRule<br/>TLS: ISTIO_MUTUAL
        Operator->>K8sAPI: Create AuthorizationPolicy
        Operator->>K8sAPI: Create Authorino AuthConfig
    end

    Note over Client,DB: Flow 3: Admission Webhook Validation

    participant APIServer as Kubernetes API Server
    participant Webhook as Webhook Server<br/>9443/TCP HTTPS

    APIServer->>Webhook: AdmissionReview<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS1.2+<br/>mTLS (API server client cert)
    Webhook->>Webhook: Validate ModelRegistry Spec<br/>Check unique name
    Webhook-->>APIServer: AdmissionReview Response<br/>Allowed: true/false
